<kml>
<concept name=Chemical-Formula>
<system-documentation=Chemical-Formula>

<superconcept name=Thing>
  <definition>
  A Chemical-Formula is a linearly ordered collection of pairs of subscript and Chemical-Entity.
  </definition>

<recquireslotlist>
  <slotdescription name=term>
     The sequence of terms in the chemical formula.
  </slotdescription>

</recquiredslotlist>

<musing>
Chemical-Formula is used to represent both molecular-formulae and empirical-formulae, since there is no sctutural difference between them. Note that a molecular formula is the filler of the <slot>moelcular-formula</slot> slot; similar for empirical-formula.
</musing>

</kml>

<examplesentencelist>

  <examplesentence>
     <text>Water, H<sub>2</sub>O, contains twice more atoms of hydrogen than of oxygen</text>
     <slotdescription name=term>(2 H), (1 O)</slotdesctiption>
  </examplesentence>

  <examplesentence>
     <text>he played the trumps in sequence</text>
